# Mobs

## When adding a new mob scene, you must (in one change set)

1. Add `mob_<name>.tscn` that uses script `res://entities/mob/mob.gd` and `class_name Mob`.
2. Add a `PackedScene` constant and branch in `game/balance/mob_spawn_selector.gd` (`MobSpawnSelector.pick_scene`).
3. Update `game/balance/default_balance_table.tres` (or the active `BalanceTable`) so spawn ratios / flags can select the new mob.
4. Keep mob body `PhysicsLayers.apply_mob_body` (`layer=2`, `mask=2`) unless you also update `game/physics_layers.gd` and all weapon/projectile masks.
5. Append the scene to `ScenePool.MOB_SCENES` in `game/pool/scene_pool.gd` for prewarm.

If you skip step 2 or 3, the mob will never spawn in play.

## Must not

- Do not duplicate AI, damage, poison, or death logic in new `.gd` files under `entities/mob/`. Visual-only children (e.g. `mob_speed_trail.gd` on `mob_fast.tscn`) are allowed; they must not call combat, spawn, or pool APIs on the parent.
- Do not spawn mobs without going through `Game.spawn_mob()` → `MobSpawnSelector.pick_scene` → `initialize_spawn_health(hp_multiplier)`.
- Do not `queue_free()` mobs at death; use `PoolUtil.release_node(self)` in `_die()` after kill/exp-orb logic.
- Do not remove `add_to_group("mobs")` from `mob.gd` `pool_on_acquire` (not `_ready`).

## Must (variant scenes)

- Differentiate variants only via `.tscn` exports (`base_max_health`, `speed_min`/`speed_max`, `mob_kind`, `slime_tint`, optional `%TargetIndicator` offset/scale) and optional visual-only child scenes (e.g. `mob_speed_trail.tscn` on fast).
- Boss/special/elite/ranged/fast scenes must remain instantiable as `Mob`.
- Every play mob scene must include `%TargetIndicator` (`Node2D` + `target_indicator_ring.gd`, default hidden) for `gun.gd` `set_targeted`. Do not revert to `circle.png` `Sprite2D` for targeting FX.
- Mob `%HealthBar` must start hidden per spawn (`initialize_spawn_health` / `pool_reset`); reveal on damage via `_reveal_health_bar`; hide on `_request_die` (pool reuse — do not `queue_free` the bar).
- Mob `CollisionShape2D` size is driven at runtime by `GroundShadowFootprint` from `%Slime` child `GroundShadow` (`pool_on_acquire` → `_sync_body_collision_to_shadow`). Do not rely on a static circle-only shape for contact standoff.
- When changing `chase_distance`, `attack_distance`, `contact_attack_interval`, `contact_attack_damage`, `CONTACT_STANDOFF_PADDING`, `CHASE_DEFAULT_INSET`, or `GroundShadow` scale, verify chase stop vs attack range — player damage uses center distance ≤ `get_contact_attack_distance()` (`_get_attack_range_distance()`); chase stop uses `_get_chase_stop_distance()` (capped at attack range). Ranged windup uses attack range, not chase stop. Ranged mobs (`ranged_attack_enabled`) must not deal contact damage.

## Must (ranged — `mob_ranged.tscn`)

- Set `ranged_attack_enabled = true` on the scene only; do not add a separate mob AI script.
- Optional child nodes: `AttackRangeRing` (visual), telegraph uses pooled `mob_attack_mark` (not a permanent scene child).
- Ranged attack flow lives in `mob.gd`: windup mark → `ranged_telegraph_delay` → `mob_projectile`; cancel mark on `pool_reset` / `_request_die`.
- Player hit uses `player.apply_mob_projectile_damage`, not `Mob.apply_weapon_damage`. Do not re-enable contact damage for ranged mobs (`is_contact_damage_active` excludes `ranged_attack_enabled`).
- `mob_projectile`: `PhysicsLayers.apply_mob_projectile` (`mask=9` = environment + player). Do not set mask to environment only — player is on layer 8.
- Spawn requires `ranged_spawn_ratio` in active `BalanceTable` (default table: from minute 8, VS형 A).

## When editing balance-driven spawn

- If you add a new spawn category, you must extend `BalancePhase` fields, `BalanceTable._finalize_phase` / `_normalize_spawn_ratios`, and `default_balance_table.tres` together.
- Do not assume linear interpolation for `boss_spawn_enabled` or `special_mob_count`; they use step resolution in `BalanceTable`.

## Death and HUD

- Do not bypass `_request_die()` / `_die()` for kill counting, smoke, exp orb drops, or magnet drops.
- Exp orbs must spawn via `ScenePool.acquire(EXP_ORB_SCENE, parent)` when `ObjectPools` exists.
- Magnet / health pickups: independent `MAGNET_DROP_CHANCE` / `HEALTH_DROP_CHANCE` (default 0.01 each) via `instantiate` (not pooled); offset spawn so pickups do not fully overlap the exp orb.
